dataIdInfo.idPurp: This dataset identifies parcels of property on the Umatilla Indian Reservation. The development of this dataset was a joint effort between the BLM lands office in Portland, Oregon, the Umatilla BIA agency office and the GIS Program at the Umatilla Indian Reservation. The dataset was created in 2006 and is maintained by the GIS Program. GCDB points were used as the corner points for allotments with alloquate parts descriptions. Parcels with survey descriptions were encoded based on the bearings and distances described within those descriptions. As new parcels are created, surveyed or partitioned that information is encoded into the dataset.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: The development of this dataset was a joint effort between the BLM lands office in Portland, Oregon, the Umatilla BIA agency office and the GIS Program at the Umatilla Indian Reservation. The dataset was created in 2006 and is maintained by the GIS Program.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Recorded allotment number as identified by the BIA.
Land ownership class of which there are 4 for the reservation. A = Individual Indian Allotment, T = Tribal Trust Allotment, TF = Tribal Fee parcel, F = Fee parcel
Umatilla County maping taxlot identification number. Is a 13 digit string identifier.

This field identifies the geographic source of the parcel. It is an indicator of the accuracy of the information used to geographically identifiy the location of the parcel. There are a variety of sources of geographic information including, BLM Portland = the BLM Portalnd office identified this location by survey descriptions., GCDB = this parcel is decribed by alloquate parts and is therefore tied to the the GCBD coordiantes grid. SURVEY = there was a survey description for this parcel and the GIS Program incoded this parcel using that survey description. AERIAL = there is no informatin available for this parcel, Umatilla County plat maps were used to identify this parcels location relative to the surrounding parcels. PUD-89-01 is an example of the CTUIR's Planning Office file numbering system for identifying new parcels. A survey plat would be included in this file and the survey plat was used to identify the geogrpahic location of this parcel.

The source of the GEOSOURCE field. There are numerous offices which provide geographic records of parcels on the reservation including DECD, Planning Office, Umatilla County Records, BIA. This field is also used to record the fiel number which tha Planning Office may use to file a partition or a PUD.

This field identifies if the purchase of this property was on contract with the prperty owner. Only Tribal Fee properties would be purchased under a contract. The DECD office identifies if this is a contracted piece of property.
This field records the acreage as recorded by the county or the BIA. This information may come from a Deed or a TSR.
This is the acres as calculated by the ArcGIS geoprocessing tool.
This field identifies the property purchasing title often used by offices within CTUIR government.
Thisi s a field with a hyperlink to the stored TSR.
This is a field which combines allotment number and taxlot number into one field. This field is used by various web applications.
Identifies any existing address on the parcel.
Records the user id of the last person to edit the record.
Records the last edited date for a record.
